                    <p change="#d2e380 #d2e400" xml:id="p_6.d2e136" xml:lang="en">Private URIs using the <code change="#d2e380 #d2e400" xml:id="code_1.d2e138" xml:lang="en">bibl:</code> prefix are pointers to bibliographic entries (<gi change="#d2e380 #d2e400" xml:id="gi_7.d2e140" xml:lang="en">bibl</gi> or <gi change="#d2e380 #d2e400" xml:id="gi_8.d2e142" xml:lang="en">biblStruct</gi>) in an external master file. For example, <code change="#d2e380 #d2e400" xml:id="code_2.d2e144" xml:lang="en">bibl:biblStruct_1.d1e1263</code> dereferences to <code change="#d2e380 #d2e400" xml:id="code_3.d2e146" xml:lang="en">oclc_644997575-master_bibliography.TEIP5.xml#bibl:biblStruct_1.d1e1263</code>.</p>
